  <front>
   <head>Jordan</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quintet">
     <l n="1" met="++-+-+--++|-+-+-+--++">Who says that fictions only and false hair</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+-+-+-+-+-">Become a verse? Is there in truth no beauty?</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+++---+-+">Is all good structure in a winding stair?</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+++-+-+-+-">May no lines pass, except they do their duty</l>
     <l n="5" met="+--+-+-+">Not to a true, but painted chair?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quintet">
     <l n="6" met="+-++-+-+-+|--++-+-+-+">Is it no verse, except enchanted groves</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+-+-+-+++">And sudden arbors shadow coarse-spun lines?</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+-+-+-+-+">Must purling streams refresh a lover's loves?</l>
     <l n="9" met="-+-+-+-+-+">Must all be veiled, while he that reads, divines,</l>
     <l n="10" met="+--+-+-+">Catching the sense at two removes?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quintet">
     <l n="11" met="+--+-+-+-+">Shepherds are honest people; let them sing:</l>
     <l n="12" met="+--+-+-+-+">Riddle who list, for me, and pull for Prime;</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+-+-+-+-+|-+-+++---+">I envy no man's nightingale or spring;</l>
     <l n="14" met="+--+-+-+-+">Nor let them punish me with loss of rhyme,</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+-+-+-+">Who plainly say, My God, My King.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
